==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contenement
<hw>Con*ten"e*ment</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n*t⟦ecr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>con-</ets> + <ets>tenement</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>That which is held together with another thing;
that which is connected with a tenement, or thing holden, as a certain
quantity of land adjacent to a dwelling, and necessary to the reputable
enjoyment of the dwelling; appurtenance.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Content</ent>⟦br⟧
